        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 8:14AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 814 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Cotulla, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cotulla, Los Angeles, Gardendale, and Fowlerton.

This includes Interstate 35 between mile markers 58 and 75.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
